ontains changes applicable to the July and December 2013 administrations. )>>endobj25609 0 obj<</Dest[347 0 R/XYZ 90 757 null]/Next 25608 0 R/Parent 25602 0 R/Prev 25610 0 R/SE 872 0 R/Title(STAAR END-OF-COURSE REPORTING STUDENT DATA FILE FORMAT )>>endobj25610 0 obj<</Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 290 65 null]/Next 25609 0 R/Parent 25602 0 R/Prev 25611 0 R/SE 871 0 R/Title(2 of 21 )>>endobj25611 0 obj<</Count 10/Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 47 239 null]/First 25612 0 R/Last 25613 0 R/Next 25610 0 R/Parent 25602 0 R/Prev 25614 0 R/SE 870 0 R/Title(5.)>>endobj25612 0 obj<</Count 6/Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 47 239 null]/First 25632 0 R/Last 25633 0 R/Next 25613 0 R/Parent 25611 0 R/SE 880 0 R/Title(5.)>>endobj25613 0 obj<</Count 2/Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 47 143 null]/First 25630 0 R/Last 25631 0 R/Parent 25611 0 R/Prev 25612 0 R/SE 881 0 R/Title(6.)>>endobj25614 0 obj<</Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 29 267 null]/Next 25611 0 R/Parent 25602 0 R/Prev 25615 0 R/SE 869 0 R/Title(Items five and six below are changes that are applicable to additional data files provided to districts in fall 2013.  )>>endobj25615 0 obj<</Count 12/Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 47 556 null]/First 25616 0 R/Last 25617 0 R/Next 25614 0 R/Parent 25602 0 R/Prev 25618 0 R/SE 868 0 R/Title(1. )>>endobj25616 0 obj<</Count 2/Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 47 556 null]/First 25628 0 R/Last 25629 0 R/Next 25625 0 R/Parent 25615 0 R/SE 894 0 R/Title(1. )>>endobj25617 0 obj<</Count 2/Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 47 349 null]/First 25620 0 R/Last 25621 0 R/Parent 25615 0 R/Prev 25622 0 R/SE 897 0 R/Title(4. )>>endobj25618 0 obj<</Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 29 584 null]/Next 25615 0 R/Parent 25602 0 R/Prev 25619 0 R/SE 867 0 R/Title(Following is a list of the most significant changes being implemented in 2013. )>>endobj25619 0 obj<</Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 29 681 null]/Next 25618 0 R/Parent 25602 0 R/Prev 25603 0 R/SE 866 0 R/Title(All STAAR, STAAR L, STAAR Modified, and STAAR Alternate data for end-of-course assessments will be reported on the same data file \(STAAR Modified and STAAR Alternate are only administered during the spring administration\). There will be one record on th\e data file for each subject for which a student is assessed. For STAAR and STAAR Modified English I, II, and III, reading and writing results will be in separate records. For STAAR Alternate English I, II, and III, there will not be separate records for \read)>>endobj25620 0 obj<</Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 47 349 null]/Next 25621 0 R/Parent 25617 0 R/SE 898 0 R/Title(4. )>>endobj25621 0 obj<</Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 59 350 null]/Parent 25617 0 R/Prev 25620 0 R/SE 899 0 R/Title(Item correct responses and studentÉs responses: Because the tests will be released in 2013 for the primary administrations \(excluding STAAR L, STAAR Modified, and Braille tests\), the correct responses will be provided on the data file and the student re\sponses will be formatted such that, if the studentÉs response is incorrect, the response that the student chose will be shown. The studentÉs responses can be found in positions 499ů566 and the correct responses can be found in positions 567ů534. )>>endobj25622 0 obj<</Count 2/Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 47 418 null]/First 25623 0 R/Last 25624 0 R/Next 25617 0 R/Parent 25615 0 R/Prev 25625 0 R/SE 896 0 R/Title(3. )>>endobj25623 0 obj<</Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 47 418 null]/Next 25624 0 R/Parent 25622 0 R/SE 900 0 R/Title(3. )>>endobj25624 0 obj<</Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 59 419 null]/Parent 25622 0 R/Prev 25623 0 R/SE 901 0 R/Title(StudentÉs performance level results at all applicable standards: The phase-in 2 standard has been added to the data file. There are three performance standards at Minimum and Level II \(phase-in 1, phase-in 2, and recommended\) and two performance standar\ds at Level III \(phase-in and recommended for Algebra II and English III reading and writing\). These values can be found in positions 392ů399. )>>endobj25625 0 obj<</Count 2/Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 47 487 null]/First 25626 0 R/Last 25627 0 R/Next 25622 0 R/Parent 25615 0 R/Prev 25616 0 R/SE 895 0 R/Title(2. )>>endobj25626 0 obj<</Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 47 487 null]/Next 25627 0 R/Parent 25625 0 R/SE 902 0 R/Title(2. )>>endobj25627 0 obj<</Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 59 488 null]/Parent 25625 0 R/Prev 25626 0 R/SE 903 0 R/Title(StudentÉs performance level results: The studentÉs performance level results \(Minimum, Level II, and Level III\) will be provided in positions 389ů391. The studentÉs performance level results will take into account the studentÉs passing standards, allowi\ng school districts to look in one location on the data file for the studentÉs results. )>>endobj25628 0 obj<</Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 47 556 null]/Next 25629 0 R/Parent 25616 0 R/SE 904 0 R/Title(1. )>>endobj25629 0 obj<</Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 59 557 null]/Parent 25616 0 R/Prev 25628 0 R/SE 905 0 R/Title(StudentÉs passing standards for Level II and Level III: The phase-in 1 standard will remain in effect through the 2013ů2014 school year. The phase-in 2 and recommended standards will be implemented in the future. The standard that the student has been ass\igned will be provided in positions 387 \(Level II\) and 388 \(Level III\). )>>endobj25630 0 obj<</Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 47 143 null]/Next 25631 0 R/Parent 25613 0 R/SE 882 0 R/Title(6.)>>endobj25631 0 obj<</Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 56 143 null]/Parent 25613 0 R/Prev 25630 0 R/SE 883 0 R/Title( Raw Scores for STAAR Modified World History: Raw scores have been added to data file for students that took the STAAR Modified world history assessment. Because world history will no longer be assessed as a result of House Bill 5, standards for the asses\sment were not set and performance level results \(Level II: Satisfactory and Level III: Advanced\) will not be reported for these students. )>>endobj25632 0 obj<</Count 2/Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 47 239 null]/First 25636 0 R/Last 25637 0 R/Next 25633 0 R/Parent 25612 0 R/SE 884 0 R/Title(5.)>>endobj25633 0 obj<</Count 2/Dest[344 0 R/XYZ 58 184 null]/First 25634 0 R/Last 25634 0 R/Parent 25612 0 R/Prev 256